div.font:
Store passwords securely with:
```sql
INSERT INTO user (
username,
password
) VALUES (
'some_username',
crypt(
'some_password',
gen_salt('bf')
)
);
```
Retrieve with:
```sql
SELECT id
FROM user
WHERE username = 'some_username'
AND password = crypt(
'some_password,
password
);
```

div.font:
A Shared User is simply a
non-login User, that multiple login Users can act as. This means a login User can have their own Accounts & Envelopes, then they can click a button to manage the Accounts & Envelopes of a Shared User that one or more other people may be able to manage as well.
This is modeled as a one to many relationship between User & itself, managed in a shared_user table that lists the pairs of user_ids.
